he's coming out to take
a look at the operation.

13:39.967 --> 13:41.033
The pressure's on.

13:42.567 --> 13:47.400
It's starting to get cold
way earlier than usual.

13:47.467 --> 13:49.667
<i>It's 22 degrees this morning.</i>

13:51.400 --> 13:53.400
[man speaking]

13:53.467 --> 13:55.900
[Shawn] <i>Gonna be tough.</i>
<i>We're gonna have</i>
<i>to fight through it.</i>

13:55.967 --> 14:00.266
<i>We're in a really hot spot.</i>
<i>I got the drill logs</i>
<i>and drill holes.</i>

14:00.266 --> 14:04.000
<i>As long as we keep</i>
<i>everything working on here</i>
<i>and everything running,</i>

14:04.066 --> 14:05.600
<i>we'll get it.</i>

14:05.667 --> 14:08.767
Nate's got the spud
hanging on the crane.

14:08.767 --> 14:12.667
<i>Drop the spud in, get a new</i>
<i>bottom cable on, go mining.</i>

14:14.100 --> 14:17.467
When you got a behemoth
as big as the <i>Myrtle,</i>
anchors are no good.

14:18.700 --> 14:21.667
<i>Instead we got two</i>
<i>60,000 pound spuds.</i>

14:23.000 --> 14:25.266
<i>They get raised</i>
<i>and lowered</i>
<i>with steel cables</i>

14:25.266 --> 14:27.300
<i>to keep the</i> Myrtle <i>in place</i>
<i>while she's digging.</i>

14:29.567 --> 14:33.567
One of the spuds
cracked the pocket
that holds it in place.

14:33.567 --> 14:36.300
<i>We got her patched up</i>
<i>but now comes the hard part.</i>

14:36.367 --> 14:39.200
<i>We gotta get that</i>
<i>spud back in place.</i>

14:39.266 --> 14:41.266
<i>It's a tiny bull's-eye</i>
<i>that we have to hit.</i>

14:42.867 --> 14:44.100
It's a pain in the ass.

14:44.100 --> 14:46.767
It's heavy, big,
it's dangerous.

14:46.767 --> 14:48.166
[radio crackling]

14:48.166 --> 14:51.667
Okay, go ahead and go
in lightly towards the ramp.

14:52.166 --> 14:53.734
[man on radio]

14:56.266 --> 15:00.500
[Shawn] <i>Once we get it</i>
<i>in this pocket, then we'll</i>
<i>be good but...</i>

15:00.567 --> 15:03.367
we gotta get it dropped down
and in the pocket, so...

15:05.300 --> 15:06.467
Okay, keep her there?

15:09.567 --> 15:10.467
<i>All right, we're good then.</i>

15:14.200 --> 15:16.367
<i>One step closer.</i>

15:16.367 --> 15:19.400
Drop the spud down,
thread the new cable,

15:19.467 --> 15:21.166
wind 'em up, tighten 'em up,

15:22.100 --> 15:22.867
go mining.

15:24.667 --> 15:26.300
[speaking]

15:28.200 --> 15:30.767
Torch. [laughs]

15:31.667 --> 15:33.266
Okay, it's good.

15:34.066 --> 15:35.500
Okay. Down?

15:36.867 --> 15:38.066
Here we go.

15:39.500 --> 15:40.200
[speaking]

15:40.266 --> 15:42.000
[crane creaking]

15:42.467 --> 15:44.266
[Shawn speaking]

16:04.600 --> 16:05.367
[Shawn laughs triumphantly]

16:06.066 --> 16:07.367
We're done!

16:07.367 --> 16:09.100
All good.
Everything went good.

16:10.000 --> 16:11.100
[man speaking]

16:12.066 --> 16:13.400
[Shawn speaking]

16:17.367 --> 16:18.667
Yeah!

16:20.266 --> 16:21.367
We got her all put
back together.

16:21.367 --> 16:23.200
She's nice and healthy.

16:23.266 --> 16:26.600
<i>It's time to get back</i>
<i>out on the top cut,</i>
<i>back on that pastry,</i>

16:26.667 --> 16:27.867
<i>and load up the box.</i>

16:29.000 --> 16:31.867
'Cause Dave will be out here,
breathing down my neck.

16:31.867 --> 16:33.700
It's time to make
every moment count.

16:34.166 --> 16:35.100
Crane's off.

16:37.367 --> 16:39.166
We're good to go.

16:39.166 --> 16:42.100
Beautiful day out. We need
to get out and get mining.

16:43.200 --> 16:44.800
[laughs]

16:44.867 --> 16:46.967
[narrator] <i>While Shawn gets</i>
<i>the</i> Myrtle <i>back to work...</i>

16:47.567 --> 16:49.567
[ticking]

16:55.500 --> 16:56.700
[narrator] <i>...on the other</i>
<i>side of the harbor...</i>

17:01.000 --> 17:03.667
[Vernon] <i>So, I got</i>
<i>to fly out of here.</i>

17:03.667 --> 17:07.000
I gotta attend a funeral
back in the Carolinas.

17:07.500 --> 17:08.467
<i>But, uh...</i>

17:08.467 --> 17:10.100
[speaking]

17:13.166 --> 17:17.500
And I feel, um,
very comfortable
leaving it with them.

17:17.567 --> 17:20.867
[narrator] <i>After weeks,</i>
<i>struggling to put many</i>
<i>points on the board,</i>

17:20.867 --> 17:25.400
<i>Vernon Adkison's hoping</i>
<i>a last minute audible</i>
<i>will motivate his team.</i>

17:25.467 --> 17:27.600
[Bryan speaking]

17:28.667 --> 17:29.567
[man] Looks pretty good.

17:31.700 --> 17:32.700
[engine starts]

17:32.767 --> 17:34.667
Another day at controls
of the gold ship,

17:34.667 --> 17:36.867
I feel confident taking
it in and out now.

17:38.266 --> 17:40.200
I'll go away, come back,

17:40.266 --> 17:44.200
there'll be gold in the box
waiting for me. I like that.

17:44.266 --> 17:46.700
Conceivably, there'll
come a point

17:46.767 --> 17:48.367
where I can just call it in

17:48.367 --> 17:51.166
and come into town every
now and then and pick
up my gold and,

17:51.166 --> 17:53.266
head back to the Hawaiian
Islands or Tahiti,

17:53.266 --> 17:54.467
or some damn place.

17:57.700 --> 18:00.367
But, who knows?
I mean, it's so
much fun in Nome.

18:00.367 --> 18:03.467
I mean, what's Tahiti got
that Nome doesn't have?

18:06.066 --> 18:07.900
Well, hula girls,
palm trees...

18:09.266 --> 18:12.767
One thing they don't
have in Tahiti is gold.

18:13.600 --> 18:15.600
<i>Not that I know of anyway.</i>

18:15.667 --> 18:19.467
<i>I was aiming for 300 ounces.</i>
<i>I've got less than 20 so far.</i>

18:19.467 --> 18:22.100
So, maybe putting
the guys in the hot seat

18:22.100 --> 18:23.667
to prove themselves

18:23.667 --> 18:27.266
<i>will finally swing</i>
<i>the pendulum</i>
<i>in our direction,</i>

18:27.266 --> 18:30.800
and we'll have some good
fortune for the rest
of the season.

18:30.867 --> 18:32.233
Season's short.

18:32.233 --> 18:35.367
We need to get as
much gold as we can
in the little time we got.

18:35.367 --> 18:39.100
So, um, tell ya,
for what it's worth.
I'm not gonna be here.

18:39.166 --> 18:41.166
So, you're gonna have
to police yourself

18:41.166 --> 18:42.567
and figure it out
for yourself.

18:42.567 --> 18:44.266
<i>Thomas has been my tender</i>

18:44.266 --> 18:46.667
<i>but now he's gonna</i>
<i>be piloting the boat.</i>

18:46.667 --> 18:48.800
And that's no
walk in the park.

18:48.867 --> 18:51.000
<i>Bryan is a ferocious diver</i>

18:51.066 --> 18:54.700
but now he'll be in charge
of keeping the system humming.

18:54.767 --> 18:57.200
<i>And Gary, he's</i>
<i>my gold gorilla.</i>

18:57.967 --> 18:59.667
He's gonna keep
feeding 'em gold

18:59.667 --> 19:03.800
and he better stay hungry
because the end of the season
is nipping on my ass.

19:03.867 --> 19:07.266
Anyway, that's about all
I got, guys, uh...

19:07.266 --> 19:09.467
About time to get
to the airport.

19:09.467 --> 19:11.500
<i>Training wheels are off</i>
<i>and I gotta say,</i>

19:11.567 --> 19:15.500
my chances of a successful
season hinges on today.

19:16.166 --> 19:17.300
[engine revving]

19:18.367 --> 19:20.500
[Vernon] <i>That's it.</i>

19:20.567 --> 19:25.000
<i>Everybody's all</i>
<i>trained up to a high</i>
<i>degree of proficiency.</i>

19:25.066 --> 19:28.200
<i>Hopefully when I get</i>
<i>back I'll be richer</i>
<i>than I am right now.</i>

19:31.767 --> 19:32.967
[narrator]
<i>Across the harbor...</i>

19:36.767 --> 19:39.367
<i>change is also</i>
<i>in the air</i>
<i>for another team.</i>

19:40.767 --> 19:42.367
[Emily] <i>Rick took off.</i>

19:42.367 --> 19:46.066
We, uh, we're finishing out
the season with a, uh,
a new diver in the boat.

19:46.066 --> 19:47.066
At least new this season.

19:47.066 --> 19:48.066
<i>Jeff, he's awesome.</i>

19:48.066 --> 19:49.767
We're on really good
gold right now.

19:49.767 --> 19:51.166
Hopefully we can
get back to it today.

19:51.867 --> 19:53.900
Jane, ready to go mine some G?

19:55.100 --> 19:56.400
Shotty. Come.

19:56.467 --> 19:57.834
[barking]

19:57.834 --> 19:59.600
[narrator]
<i>With the homestretch</i>
<i>of summer in her sights,</i>

19:59.667 --> 20:02.066
<i>Emily Riedel is bringing</i>
<i>in a heavyweight</i>

20:02.066 --> 20:04.767
<i>to keep momentum on her side.</i>

20:04.767 --> 20:06.734
[Emily] <i>I'm gonna</i>
<i>come out with Jane.</i>

20:06.734 --> 20:10.367
<i>Since Jeff's back on the boat</i>
<i>for the first time, Alex and I</i>
<i>are gonna go out and, uh,</i>

20:10.367 --> 20:11.200
<i>get him all set up.</i>

20:11.800 --> 20:12.867
[speaking]

20:12.867 --> 20:14.066
-How you doing?
-[Jane] Hi.

20:15.200 --> 20:16.300
-Nice to meet you.
-Yes!

20:16.367 --> 20:18.867
-Doing good? Awesome.
-[Jane] Yeah.

20:18.867 --> 20:22.467
[Emily] <i>It's crunch time.</i>
<i>We've had an awesome</i>
<i>season so far but,</i>

20:22.467 --> 20:25.600
in order to hit 250 ounces,
we've got to finish strong.

20:25.667 --> 20:28.100
<i>-So, Rick's gone now.</i>
-[buzzer sound]

20:28.100 --> 20:30.367
I'm calling in my buddy
Jeff Orzechowski.

20:30.367 --> 20:32.900
<i>-He's always produced</i>
<i>awesome gold for</i> The Eroica.
-[applause]

20:32.967 --> 20:34.667
He's my ace in the hole
here at the end of the season.

20:34.667 --> 20:37.066
And I know that Jeff's
gonna get us there.

20:37.066 --> 20:38.600
There we go.
Life's short, right?

20:38.667 --> 20:40.900
-[Emily] Yes.
-[Jeff on radio] <i>Looking</i>
<i>really good.</i>

20:40.967 --> 20:42.867
<i>We can put another ounce</i>
<i>in the box.</i>

20:42.867 --> 20:44.266
-[Jane] Wow.
-All right, well, you're gonna

20:44.266 --> 20:45.600
be taking care
of me today, huh?

20:45.667 --> 20:47.467
-[Jane] I do.
-[Jeff] All right.

20:49.467 --> 20:52.000
[Emily] <i>The plan this winter</i>
<i>is for Jane to take over</i>

20:52.066 --> 20:54.867
<i>when I have the baby.</i>
<i>I still need to be confident</i>

20:54.867 --> 20:57.367
that Jane can step up
into that position.

20:57.367 --> 20:59.467
<i>And I really need to,</i>
<i>like, watch her closely</i>

20:59.467 --> 21:01.967
<i>and analyze just to make sure</i>
<i>that this is gonna work.</i>

21:01.967 --> 21:04.200
Yeah, the pressure is on
for both of us.

21:05.100 --> 21:06.667
[Jane speaking]

21:07.300 --> 21:09.166
You what?

21:09.166 --> 21:10.700
-How to get a rock jam out?
-[Jane speaking]

21:10.767 --> 21:11.767
[Jane chuckles]

21:11.767 --> 21:13.467
Well, hopefully,
we won't get any of those.

21:15.367 --> 21:17.967
[Jane] <i>I'm excited.</i>
<i>I'm working with a new diver.</i>

21:17.967 --> 21:20.500
He sounds like he knows
what he's doing,
so that's good.

21:20.567 --> 21:23.667
And, um, 'cause like,
there's gonna be a lot
of trust involved

21:23.667 --> 21:27.867
and I would want him
to feel like he's safe
under water with me.

21:29.667 --> 21:32.567
I had a dream last night
that we found, like,
a bunch of big nuggets.

21:32.567 --> 21:35.000
-[man exclaims]
-I was-- But I was,
like, down diving

21:35.000 --> 21:37.300
with a garden hose for some
reason, and I was like--

21:37.367 --> 21:39.567
It was like the garden hose
size suction device.

21:39.567 --> 21:41.367
-[man] Sticking on gold to it?
-And I kept-- Yeah, I know,

21:41.367 --> 21:43.367
it was a little thin
and I kept finding
all these big nuggets,

21:43.367 --> 21:44.667
and sucking 'em up
like... [mimics]

21:55.367 --> 21:57.066
[Jane] And I'm happy
to be of assistance

21:57.066 --> 21:58.600
if you need any help.

21:58.667 --> 22:00.567
<i>I thought I'd get used</i>
<i>to the new diver,</i>

22:00.567 --> 22:03.000
so I'm just kinda
following around right now,

22:03.066 --> 22:05.000
like, forcing myself for him
to, like, get to know me

22:05.000 --> 22:06.400
and, um, think that I'm fun.

22:06.467 --> 22:08.300
Really run right now. [sighs]

22:08.867 --> 22:10.467
Just doing chores.

22:10.467 --> 22:12.800
I'm kinda materialistic
and shallow sometimes,

22:12.867 --> 22:16.567
and I just need to be like...
[stutters] I'm a good person.

22:16.567 --> 22:19.667
So trust me.
[laughing] Hell [bleep] no.

22:20.300 --> 22:21.166
Oh.

22:25.166 --> 22:26.567
Just two or three?

22:29.700 --> 22:31.467
[Jane] Oh, I see.

22:31.467 --> 22:33.967
<i>Yeah, they're setting</i>
<i>three anchors out here.</i>

22:33.967 --> 22:35.667
Well, a skiff's gonna
take one anchor out

22:35.667 --> 22:37.166
<i>and kinda just put it</i>
<i>where they want it.</i>

22:37.667 --> 22:39.400
Jiminy Crickets.

22:39.467 --> 22:41.166
<i>I'm not used to boats</i>
<i>having three anchors</i>

22:41.166 --> 22:43.767
<i>but this dredge is gotta</i>
<i>have it so it can, like,</i>

22:43.767 --> 22:45.500
<i>stay in the place that</i>
<i>we want, which is, like,</i>

22:45.567 --> 22:46.967
<i>hopefully, right on the gold.</i>

22:46.967 --> 22:47.800
Okay, good.

22:49.367 --> 22:51.467
But sometimes I also feel like

22:52.300 --> 22:53.400
there's a soap opera in Nome

22:53.467 --> 22:55.066
and I call it
"As the Anchor Drags".

22:55.166 --> 22:57.166
[instrumental music playing]

23:14.100 --> 23:15.367
[Jane] Total soap opera.

23:16.600 --> 23:18.000
The diver's getting naked.

23:18.000 --> 23:19.800
Well, I mean,
he's changing his clothes.

23:19.867 --> 23:21.467
So I'm giving him his privacy.

23:21.467 --> 23:23.567
His privacy?

23:23.567 --> 23:25.800
Got married women
on this boat.
Can't be looking.

23:27.100 --> 23:27.900
[laughs]

23:33.066 --> 23:34.367
[Emily] Yeah,
we're good to go.

23:34.367 --> 23:35.400
[Jeff speaking]

24:00.867 --> 24:02.667
[Emily] What-- What's
it look like, <i>jefe?</i>

24:02.667 --> 24:03.867
[Jeff speaking]

24:07.867 --> 24:08.867
[Emily] <i>Oh, nice.</i>

24:09.467 --> 24:10.867
[Jeff speaking]

24:13.900 --> 24:15.800
[Emily] <i>All right,</i>
<i>poke away, brother.</i>

24:15.867 --> 24:17.467
[Jane] Oh, boy.

24:17.467 --> 24:20.166
This is a good spot for gold.

24:22.100 --> 24:25.767
Think it's 'cause of me.
I'm like the good luck
charm on the boat.

24:25.767 --> 24:27.767
Really wasn't any gold
until I showed up.

24:29.767 --> 24:31.800
It's true story, puppy.
Just remember that.

24:32.400 --> 24:33.867
[dog whimpering]

24:34.767 --> 24:35.867
[Jeff speaking]

24:36.900 --> 24:39.200
[Emily] Yeah, hopefully,
we'll make money today.

24:40.767 --> 24:42.367
[Jane] <i>Rockin' and rollin'</i>
<i>down there.</i>

24:52.100 --> 24:53.066
[Zeke] What up?

24:53.066 --> 24:55.467
-Hey, brother.
-Hey, glad you made it.

24:55.467 --> 24:57.467
-Yeah.
-Did-- Did they
find your bags?

24:57.467 --> 24:59.100
-Oh, they lost 'em.
It'll be on the next flight.
-Oh, okay.

24:59.100 --> 25:00.567
-All right, run on.
-Yeah, gonna grab those

25:00.567 --> 25:01.867
-bags there.
-[Zeke] Sounds good.

25:01.867 --> 25:04.100
[narrator] <i>After suddenly</i>
<i>losing his tender,</i>

25:04.100 --> 25:05.867
<i>Zeke Tenhoff's hoping</i>
<i>to catch lightning</i>

25:05.867 --> 25:08.367
<i>in a bottle</i>
<i>with a new recruit.</i>

25:08.367 --> 25:10.266
[Zeke] Right on, you made it.

25:10.266 --> 25:12.867
My back is up against the wall
since Steve quit on me,

25:12.867 --> 25:16.467
<i>so I called in a favor</i>
<i>and I'm bringing up</i>
<i>my friend, Nate, to help.</i>

25:16.467 --> 25:19.567
<i>Nate's just a really intense</i>
<i>high energy guy.</i>

25:19.567 --> 25:22.300
<i>He's real tough, he's been</i>
<i>on crab boats a lot.</i>

25:22.367 --> 25:24.767
<i>But most importantly,</i>
<i>he's a certified diver.</i>

25:24.767 --> 25:26.900
But he's never dredged
for gold before.

25:26.967 --> 25:28.567
So hopefully,
he catches on quick.

25:29.200 --> 25:30.266
[Nate speaking]

25:32.567 --> 25:33.400
How was the bungee jump?

25:34.400 --> 25:35.100
Nice.

25:40.300 --> 25:41.200
[Zeke chuckles]

25:41.266 --> 25:42.166
[Nate] So good.

25:45.100 --> 25:46.767
Brush your teeth.

25:46.767 --> 25:48.800
That's a daily reminder
right there, folks.

25:48.867 --> 25:50.700
You only get one set.

25:50.767 --> 25:53.667
I'm definitely flipping
the script getting
Nate on board.

25:53.667 --> 25:56.100
<i>He's got a real</i>
<i>can do positive attitude.</i>

25:56.100 --> 25:58.767
<i>He really wants</i>
<i>to be involved.</i>
<i>Totally different vibe.</i>

25:58.767 --> 26:01.567
[Nate] They don't call me
Nine Finger Nate for nothing.

26:02.166 --> 26:03.667
I'm missing a finger.

26:03.667 --> 26:05.967
The thing about
Nine Fingers Nate
is he's not gonna

26:05.967 --> 26:08.200
bitch and moan about
things like Steve Riedel.

26:08.266 --> 26:10.767
And so hopefully, like,
that good positive attitude

26:10.767 --> 26:13.800
<i>will help us, uh, get</i>
<i>a lot more gold this season.</i>

26:13.867 --> 26:16.667
I need to get some more gold.
I mean, I had...

26:16.667 --> 26:19.500
That cleanup that I just
had was-- I mean,
it was a good cleanup.

26:19.567 --> 26:21.100
<i>I mean, I'll take it, like,</i>

26:21.100 --> 26:23.700
17, almost 18 ounces of gold.

26:23.767 --> 26:26.000
But I know I can do better.

26:26.066 --> 26:29.400
You know, there's--
where I left off there's more
and...

26:30.900 --> 26:33.500
We don't have a whole lot
of, uh, mining days left

26:33.567 --> 26:35.367
so I wanna make
the most of it.

26:35.367 --> 26:37.100
Ready to make some money,
get some gold.

26:38.000 --> 26:39.100
[engine starts]

26:39.900 --> 26:41.700
-Yeah.
-[Nate] Good to go.

26:51.567 --> 26:52.667
[Zeke speaking]

26:56.467 --> 26:57.700
Swing.

27:00.066 --> 27:01.867
[Zeke] <i>I'm going right back</i>
<i>out to the pay streak</i>

27:01.867 --> 27:03.467
<i>that I found last time</i>
<i>I was out.</i>

27:03.467 --> 27:05.867
I don't wanna mess around.
There's only a few days left

27:05.867 --> 27:07.767
and I wanna hit
the good stuff while I can.

27:07.767 --> 27:10.000
<i>And plus, this is gonna</i>
<i>be Nate's first dive.</i>

27:10.066 --> 27:12.567
<i>So I wanna be able</i>
<i>to know that there's</i>
<i>gonna be good gold</i>

27:12.567 --> 27:14.367
for him to see as soon
as he gets down there.

27:16.567 --> 27:17.500
Let her rip!

27:23.867 --> 27:24.767
[breathing under water]

27:36.000 --> 27:37.367
Rock and roll.

27:43.900 --> 27:45.667
How's it looking
down there, Zeke?

27:45.667 --> 27:47.200
<i>How's the visibility?</i>

27:48.166 --> 27:49.367
[Zeke speaking]

27:55.066 --> 27:55.867
Uh...

28:10.500 --> 28:11.667
Uh, hey.

28:18.667 --> 28:20.467
Talk to me, what's going on?

28:20.467 --> 28:21.667
[Zeke speaking]

28:39.767 --> 28:40.800
[Nate speaking]

28:42.266 --> 28:44.166
You know I'm saying?
That scrilla.

28:44.166 --> 28:47.000
Ducats, the moolah.

28:47.000 --> 28:50.767
Frogskins, man,
dead presidents. You know
what I'm talkin' about?

28:50.767 --> 28:51.767
Money!

28:58.667 --> 28:59.867
[narrator] <i>Ten miles east...</i>

29:03.867 --> 29:06.166
So Vern's not here today,
it's just us guys.

29:06.166 --> 29:09.200
So let's be on our game,
let's show we got initiative

29:09.266 --> 29:10.367
and let's get some
gold in the box.

29:10.367 --> 29:11.166
-[Bryan] Let's get some gold.
-Get it.

29:13.667 --> 29:14.867
[Thomas] Release.

29:14.867 --> 29:16.800
[narrator] <i>With the salty</i>
<i>skipper away,</i>

29:16.867 --> 29:19.967
<i>the</i> Wild Ranger <i>crew</i>
<i>is ready to prove their mettle</i>

29:19.967 --> 29:22.467
<i>by piling up precious metal.</i>

29:22.467 --> 29:24.967
-[man] And we're off.
-No turning back.

29:26.600 --> 29:28.400
[Thomas] <i>I hope today</i>
<i>everything goes smooth</i>

29:28.467 --> 29:30.800
<i>and goes as it does</i>
<i>while he's here.</i>

29:30.867 --> 29:33.367
Or even smoother
would be nice.

29:33.367 --> 29:35.700
That's what we're shooting
for, smoother without Vernon.

29:36.667 --> 29:38.100
<i>Let's get this done.</i>

29:38.166 --> 29:40.300
[Gary] <i>This'll be us proving</i>
<i>that, uh, you know,</i>

29:40.367 --> 29:42.967
that we really don't need
him on the boat that much.

29:42.967 --> 29:45.100
<i>I mean, we're--</i>
<i>we're a tight crew</i>

29:45.100 --> 29:47.166
<i>and I think-- I think</i>
<i>we'll do really well.</i>

29:47.166 --> 29:50.000
[Thomas] <i>Yeah, it'll be fun</i>
<i>to go prospect</i>
<i>some different areas.</i>

29:52.100 --> 29:54.000
[Bryan] <i>Vernon always</i>
<i>likes hittin' the same hole,</i>

29:54.066 --> 29:55.867
which is good, I mean,
we know there's gold there,

29:55.867 --> 29:58.467
but we want better gold.
So, um, we're gonna try

29:58.467 --> 30:00.467
some new areas, um,
since Vern's not here.

30:00.467 --> 30:02.100
We'll try
a little bit shallower,

30:02.166 --> 30:04.367
<i>maybe 8 to 12 feet of water</i>

30:04.367 --> 30:06.266
and see if, um,
we can find some cobble.

30:11.367 --> 30:15.100
[Thomas] All right.
You guys wanna
check out this area?

30:15.166 --> 30:16.967
[Gary] Yep,
put that camera down.

30:24.100 --> 30:26.000
How're we looking down there?

30:26.000 --> 30:27.967
-It's sand.
-[Bryan] That's not
what we want.

30:27.967 --> 30:29.166
We don't want sand.

30:29.166 --> 30:30.467
[Gary] We're on sand.

30:33.767 --> 30:37.767
Vern always reminds us
how much he spends
on these cameras.

30:37.767 --> 30:40.467
Let's [bleep] do it.
I don't wanna ruin
that damn camera.

30:40.467 --> 30:42.767
A damn $1,000 camera.

30:42.767 --> 30:45.467
[Thomas] <i>We're using</i>
<i>the camera under motor</i>

30:45.467 --> 30:47.767
<i>and this is, uh,</i>
<i>definitely a big no-no.</i>

30:47.767 --> 30:50.367
Just because of risk
of sucking it up
into our prop.

30:50.367 --> 30:52.200
[Vernon] Y'all didn't tell me
you put the camera down.

30:52.266 --> 30:53.767
I'm up here [bleep] with
this business.

30:53.767 --> 30:55.467
I don't wanna run that camera

30:55.467 --> 30:57.367
through the propeller
like we've done before.

30:57.367 --> 30:59.000
[Thomas] <i>And it's definitely</i>
<i>going a lot quicker</i>

30:59.000 --> 31:00.467
<i>than when Vern's on board.</i>

31:00.467 --> 31:03.000
Having to anchor up
and, you know,

31:03.000 --> 31:04.667
just bring everything
to a dead stop

31:04.667 --> 31:05.867
just so we could
drop the camera.

31:08.567 --> 31:11.266
-So we're on the cobble--
-This is working great so far.

31:11.266 --> 31:13.500
-[Gary] There's some cobble.
-This is, uh, we're going
a lot faster.

31:13.567 --> 31:15.900
I mean, we just covered
300 feet of ground already.

31:15.967 --> 31:18.500
We're on cobble and sand,
now I just seen the cobble
go by.

31:18.567 --> 31:20.100
We're on cobble sand.

31:21.100 --> 31:22.700
Nothing's wrapped up
in the propeller.

31:22.767 --> 31:24.166
[Gary] Oh, man,
this is looking good, though.

31:28.000 --> 31:29.200
I mean, we're making a map

31:29.200 --> 31:31.500
so it's gonna take
a little time
but once we do this,

31:31.567 --> 31:33.467
bang, we'll know...
We'll be going here

31:33.467 --> 31:34.800
all the time where
all of our patches are.

31:34.867 --> 31:37.000
All right, let's drop
our rear anchor.

31:37.066 --> 31:37.867
[Gary] All right.

31:41.266 --> 31:42.467
Guys, ready?

31:42.467 --> 31:43.800
You're, uh, pretty close
to be ready?

31:43.867 --> 31:45.567
-You wanna set the box?
-[Gary] I'm ready.

31:46.166 --> 31:46.800
[Bryan] Yep.

31:56.000 --> 31:56.767
[Gary] Okay.

32:08.100 --> 32:09.000
Coming down.

32:09.000 --> 32:10.166
[breathing under water]

32:20.600 --> 32:22.100
[vocalizing]

32:23.367 --> 32:24.100
[exclaims]

32:25.467 --> 32:27.166
How's your water temp, good?

32:27.166 --> 32:29.100
[Gary on radio] <i>Uh,</i>
<i>yeah, feels good so far.</i>

32:30.100 --> 32:31.233
All right.

32:32.200 --> 32:33.900
[Gary] All right. Let's take
a look around down here.

32:38.000 --> 32:39.667
[Bryan] How's the material
looking? Pretty good?

32:43.400 --> 32:45.867
[Gary] Yeah, it looks pretty
damn good from what
I'm looking at.

32:45.867 --> 32:48.467
-Awesome, let's get
some gold, buddy.
-[Gary on radio] <i>Sure.</i>

32:49.700 --> 32:52.266
How does it feel, you guys,
not having Vernon on the boat?

32:54.266 --> 32:56.900
It's a little more quieter,
that's for sure.

32:56.967 --> 32:58.300
So don't [bleep] around.

32:58.367 --> 33:00.300
[shouting] Hey,
you wanna fight, [bleep]?

33:00.367 --> 33:03.100
What do you mean,
I don't know what
I'm [bleep] doing?

33:03.100 --> 33:05.867
[Gary on radio]
<i>It's definitely more quieter.</i>

33:05.867 --> 33:08.867
[Bryan] <i>Do you think it's</i>
<i>a good way to find ground</i>
<i>from now on,</i>

33:08.867 --> 33:12.100
<i>um, you know,</i>
<i>put the camera down</i>
<i>with the boat moving?</i>

33:12.867 --> 33:14.333
[Gary] Oh, yeah.

33:16.100 --> 33:18.667
-Yeah, I think it saved
a lot of time.
-[Gary on radio] <i>Yeah.</i>

33:18.667 --> 33:20.867
[Bryan] Yeah, so far so good.
We got a guy down dredging.

33:20.867 --> 33:22.300
That's all that counts,

33:22.367 --> 33:25.000
you know, the dredge box is
going so we're getting
gold nuggets.

33:25.767 --> 33:27.000
Everything's working,
but like,

33:27.000 --> 33:28.767
you see all these lines,
you know we...

33:28.767 --> 33:31.400
Vernon'd be yelling
about all those lines
on the floor. [laughs]

33:31.467 --> 33:33.100
[Vernon] Pick that [bleep].

33:33.100 --> 33:36.567
Damn it. These cords on deck
are my pet peeve.

33:36.567 --> 33:39.166
It's a fire hazard.
You damage these cords,

33:39.166 --> 33:41.100
next thing you know,
they're sparking off.

33:41.166 --> 33:43.266
[bleep] burn you to death
in the middle of the night.

33:43.266 --> 33:45.166
[Bryan] But, uh,
everyone's safe

33:45.166 --> 33:47.000
and, uh, good day so far.

33:47.000 --> 33:47.767
We'll see, we'll see.

33:48.367 --> 33:49.367
[Gary speaking]

33:50.367 --> 33:53.066
[Bryan] Oh, yeah, baby!
Show me the gold.

33:56.367 --> 33:57.400
[clock ticking]

34:06.100 --> 34:07.100
[Dave] Oh, yeah.

34:08.467 --> 34:09.900
Back in action.

34:09.967 --> 34:12.367
I gotta watch out,
the boss is here now.

34:12.367 --> 34:14.900
Yeah, he needs to get
his ass to work.

34:14.967 --> 34:18.367
[narrator] <i>After giving</i>
<i>his golden beast</i>
<i>a clean bill of health...</i>

34:18.367 --> 34:19.867
[Shawn] We should
be good to go.

34:19.867 --> 34:22.600
[narrator] <i>...Mr. Gold</i>
<i>and</i> Myrtle <i>owner Dave Young</i>

34:22.667 --> 34:26.266
<i>are ready to release her</i>
<i>back into the wild.</i>

34:26.266 --> 34:28.967
[Dave] Just came into town.
The <i>Myrtle's</i> been broke down.

34:37.367 --> 34:38.400
Today's the day.

34:41.100 --> 34:43.000
There's always more pressure
when the boss

34:43.000 --> 34:45.467
is looking over your shoulder
breathing down your neck.

34:45.467 --> 34:47.667
<i>And thus far,</i>
<i>this season hasn't gone</i>

34:47.667 --> 34:49.700
<i>the way we planned</i>
<i>for either of us.</i>

34:50.767 --> 34:51.567
[sighs]

34:51.567 --> 34:52.700
[Dave] Forty-eight.

34:53.800 --> 34:55.967
Gotta do a little better
than that, Shawn.

34:55.967 --> 34:58.367
We got a lot of money
on the line.

34:58.367 --> 35:00.767
[Shawn] <i>This day needs</i>
<i>to be a big day for us.</i>

35:00.767 --> 35:03.900
If not, this summer
could turn out to be
on the losing end,

35:03.967 --> 35:05.767
and that could
crush us financially.

35:08.266 --> 35:10.100
Security, security, security.

35:10.100 --> 35:12.166
<i>Myrtle Irene</i> leaving
their harbor

35:12.166 --> 35:15.467
and headed for sea.
Any concerned or
closed traffic

35:15.467 --> 35:18.600
be standing by
on channel 16 and 72.

35:19.500 --> 35:20.767
Here we go, Dave.

35:24.667 --> 35:26.567
We got the-- some drill holes.

35:26.567 --> 35:28.100
I'm hoping they're
not too deep.

35:34.567 --> 35:37.000
And I think we're gonna
load some boxes.

35:43.467 --> 35:45.200
[Shawn] <i>So I'll get</i>
<i>the prime pump going</i>

35:45.266 --> 35:46.867
<i>and get fired up.</i>

35:47.867 --> 35:48.867
Here we go.

35:52.100 --> 35:53.400
Hey.

35:53.467 --> 35:55.800
Feels really good to be
back out on the water.

35:56.900 --> 35:59.567
Seems like everything's
working just fine now.

36:05.000 --> 36:07.000
I wanna load this box up.

36:07.066 --> 36:09.467
<i>Myrtle's</i> back up
and running, baby.

36:16.667 --> 36:18.100
Oh, yeah.

36:18.100 --> 36:20.567
Need some love
from the Bering Sea.

36:25.000 --> 36:27.600
Hope I can just keep
this in digging.

36:27.667 --> 36:31.500
I have a feeling, gonna give
out a good bounty this time.

36:32.800 --> 36:35.166
Fill the box up in a day.

36:35.166 --> 36:37.767
Yep, cobble to sand,
it's gonna be good.

36:38.500 --> 36:39.467
[laughs]

36:41.300 --> 36:43.000
This stuff looks amazing.

36:44.166 --> 36:45.066
Seem to be

36:46.166 --> 36:48.066
working just fine now.

36:48.066 --> 36:50.567
This looks like some
really good ground.

36:51.700 --> 36:54.300
Dave's in town
giving us a hand.

36:57.000 --> 36:59.100
Nice to see it
up and running again.

37:00.467 --> 37:03.500
Everyday we're putting gold
in the box is a good day.

37:05.066 --> 37:07.200
This is some
good-looking dirt.

37:07.266 --> 37:10.900
Now we just gotta keep
this beast running
without any breakdown.

37:13.867 --> 37:15.166
[narrator] <i>Ten miles east...</i>

37:22.867 --> 37:23.667
Hey, what's up?

37:24.200 --> 37:25.200
[Brad speaking]

37:26.266 --> 37:27.600
[Kris speaking]

37:27.667 --> 37:30.367
[Brad on radio] <i>I got good,</i>
<i>black material.</i>

37:31.467 --> 37:33.567
Okay, that's great.
Is there any gold in it?

37:35.867 --> 37:37.066
[Brad speaking]

37:38.667 --> 37:41.567
[narrator] <i>The Kellys continue</i>
<i>to swing and miss.</i>

37:42.600 --> 37:43.667
[Kris speaking]

37:45.000 --> 37:46.066
[Brad speaking]

37:51.000 --> 37:53.166
Uh, good report. I don't
think he's on gold.

37:53.166 --> 37:54.467
He's in a pissed off mood

37:54.467 --> 37:55.800
which usually tells me

37:55.867 --> 37:57.367
that he's not seeing [bleep].

37:57.367 --> 37:59.400
You know, I know
we're crazy people.

37:59.467 --> 38:01.166
So we, uh, we're not
in good moods

38:01.166 --> 38:02.667
when we don't see gold.

38:02.667 --> 38:04.800
You know, when we're--
we're working for free,

38:04.867 --> 38:06.066
we're in bad mood.

38:08.800 --> 38:11.000
And everybody's spirit
will just, like,

38:11.000 --> 38:13.667
will skyrocket. Morale will
just shoot right up.

38:16.066 --> 38:17.033
[Brad speaking]

38:20.600 --> 38:21.700
[Kris on radio] <i>Okay,</i>
<i>come on up.</i>

38:24.867 --> 38:26.867
Don't worry, don't let this
put you in a bad mood.

38:26.867 --> 38:28.266
This is nothing.

38:29.567 --> 38:31.700
You know when you get
that feeling in the pit
of your stomach

38:31.767 --> 38:33.266
when everything's
falling apart?

38:33.266 --> 38:34.767
That's how I feel right now.

38:34.767 --> 38:36.867
<i>So as the captain,</i>
<i>I need to fix</i>

38:36.867 --> 38:38.467
<i>this sinking ship myself.</i>

38:38.467 --> 38:40.767
I'm gonna do my first dive
of the season.

38:41.967 --> 38:43.200
[valiant instrumental
music playing]

38:44.867 --> 38:47.100
Great moment in the history
of the <i>Reaper.</i>

38:47.100 --> 38:48.800
Kris is back.

38:48.867 --> 38:52.500
His boat broke down,
he's going down
to put us on gold.

38:52.567 --> 38:54.767
Just like the good old days.

38:54.767 --> 38:58.100
It'd be pretty sweet
if I go down there
and save my season.

39:00.266 --> 39:01.667
That would be a baller move.

39:07.467 --> 39:10.200
All right, we just got Kris
down, I think he's on cobble.

39:10.266 --> 39:12.867
So hopefully, we got
a nice gold-packed area.

39:26.066 --> 39:27.066
[Kris speaking]

39:30.400 --> 39:32.100
All right, that's good news.

39:36.166 --> 39:37.266
[Kris speaking]

39:57.767 --> 39:59.567
Kris is on gold!

40:01.667 --> 40:02.867
Okay, get to work.

40:06.667 --> 40:07.467
Finally.

40:10.166 --> 40:11.200
[Kris speaking]

40:22.100 --> 40:23.500
[Brad] Hey, you're up
by the front of the boat.

40:23.567 --> 40:25.100
You need to come
back this way.

40:25.867 --> 40:27.000
[Kris speaking]

40:35.100 --> 40:37.467
Uh, moved a little bit
but it's stopped now.

40:40.367 --> 40:41.567
[Kris speaking]

40:44.266 --> 40:45.200
Uh...

40:47.000 --> 40:48.166
[Andy speaking]

40:55.266 --> 40:57.367
It was doing it to me too
when I was down.

41:03.200 --> 41:04.266
[Kris speaking]

41:06.100 --> 41:07.400
[Brad] What's he sayin'?

41:07.467 --> 41:08.600
That you're a dumbass.

41:08.667 --> 41:09.767
All right, he says
that all the time,

41:09.767 --> 41:11.266
he says that about everybody.

41:11.867 --> 41:12.867
[Kris speaking]

41:19.300 --> 41:20.266
[bleep], man.

41:33.166 --> 41:34.166
Always something, dude.

41:35.300 --> 41:36.500
[bleep] deja vu, dude.

41:36.567 --> 41:39.567
Back working with my dad
is a [bleep] joke.

41:39.567 --> 41:42.400
He really doesn't give
two [bleep] about
what's going on.

41:43.066 --> 41:44.100
Back here we are again.

41:44.100 --> 41:46.266
Just going in circles.

41:46.266 --> 41:47.567
[Kris speaking]

41:48.000 --> 41:48.934
We were on gold.

41:48.934 --> 41:52.700
But we have to stay there
to make it work.

41:52.767 --> 41:54.600
Is it your first day
on the boat?

41:54.667 --> 41:55.400
[Brad speaking]

41:55.400 --> 41:56.367
Well then,
what's your problem?

41:56.367 --> 41:57.667
What's your problem?

41:57.667 --> 41:59.367
[Brad speaking]

42:00.066 --> 42:01.467
Set this anchor.

42:04.200 --> 42:06.567
And then back up
until this anchor's tight.

42:07.900 --> 42:09.367
<i>You know, they have one job.</i>

42:09.367 --> 42:11.667
<i>Just keep everything</i>
<i>on top from being</i>
<i>a cluster</i> [bleep],

42:11.667 --> 42:13.066
<i>and they can't do it.</i>

42:13.066 --> 42:14.667
<i>The anchor</i>
<i>had so much slack in it</i>

42:14.667 --> 42:16.300
<i>it was dragging</i>
<i>all over the place.</i>

42:17.300 --> 42:19.100
<i>Now I lost the pay streak</i>
<i>I was on,</i>

42:19.166 --> 42:20.567
<i>and now I have to find it</i>
<i>again.</i>

42:21.767 --> 42:23.200
Even when I find the gold,

42:23.266 --> 42:24.800
they find a way
to screw it up.

42:28.166 --> 42:29.700
[Brad] Yay, he's gone.

42:31.767 --> 42:33.166
Everything's good.

42:33.166 --> 42:34.266
We're almost on gold.

42:35.500 --> 42:37.166
[Kris speaking]

42:40.667 --> 42:42.200
[Kris speaking]

42:44.667 --> 42:45.767
[Kris speaking]

42:46.900 --> 42:48.000
[Brad] Yeah, full black.

42:49.567 --> 42:50.867
Okay.

42:54.967 --> 42:56.967
[Kris speaking]

43:01.367 --> 43:04.000
[Kris speaking]

43:04.066 --> 43:05.300
We're on gold!

43:07.266 --> 43:09.367
Hey, we're on gold!

43:09.367 --> 43:12.500
Well, morale's high.
Look at these guys,
all smiles now.

43:13.100 --> 43:14.266
Miles of smiles.

43:16.266 --> 43:17.867
[Kris speaking]

43:24.467 --> 43:27.767
[laughs] It says
we're in Miami.

43:27.767 --> 43:29.166
[laughing]

43:37.767 --> 43:38.967
[narrator] <i>In Nome, Alaska,</i>

43:40.000 --> 43:44.367
<i>the pendulum swings</i>
<i>on the final days of summer.</i>

43:44.367 --> 43:48.300
<i>Now, each crew uses</i>
<i>everything they've got</i>
<i>to cash in</i>

43:48.367 --> 43:50.467
<i>before the clock</i>
<i>strikes midnight</i>

43:50.467 --> 43:51.600
<i>on their dreams.</i>

43:58.100 --> 44:00.400
[Bryan] All right, man,
you've been down four hours.

44:00.467 --> 44:01.400
How's the ground looking?

44:02.567 --> 44:03.967
[Gary speaking]

44:09.967 --> 44:11.266
Yeah, that's awesome.

44:11.266 --> 44:12.367
[narrator] <i>Without</i>
<i>their captain,</i>

44:12.400 --> 44:15.100
<i>the</i> Wild Ranger <i>crew</i>
<i>is on their own.</i>

44:15.166 --> 44:16.867
<i>And on the gold.</i>

44:16.867 --> 44:19.100
Today's the first day
without Vernon.

44:19.166 --> 44:20.667
<i>We're on good ground,</i>
<i>it looks like.</i>

44:20.667 --> 44:22.600
<i>There's a couple of inches</i>
<i>of overburden.</i>

44:23.600 --> 44:25.467
[Gary speaking]

44:31.367 --> 44:33.667
[Bryan] Yeah, man,
do you wanna come up
for a break?

44:33.667 --> 44:35.400
[Gary] <i>Okay, yeah,</i>
<i>I'm coming up right now.</i>

44:41.367 --> 44:42.800
[Bryan] <i>I don't think</i>
<i>we need to go far.</i>

44:42.867 --> 44:43.900
So we're just gonna move
the boat back,

44:43.967 --> 44:45.300
maybe a 100 feet or so,

44:45.367 --> 44:47.400
and try over there.

44:47.467 --> 44:49.066
[Gary] <i>Took the hose</i>
<i>all the way around</i>
<i>the backside of the boat.</i>

44:49.066 --> 44:51.667
<i>Worked all the way around,</i>
<i>punched about 10 holes.</i>

44:51.667 --> 44:52.867
We-- we've definitely proven

44:52.867 --> 44:54.800
that we can do this
on our own, so, uh,

44:54.867 --> 44:56.467
<i>Bryan's gonna go down</i>
<i>and uh,</i>

44:56.467 --> 44:58.567
<i>-just keep punching around.</i>
-[Bryan] <i>No problem.</i>

44:58.567 --> 45:00.800
-[motor whirring]
-You got it. There you go.

45:01.767 --> 45:02.667
Yeah. Feels good.

45:07.767 --> 45:08.867
All right. Cool.

45:20.467 --> 45:21.767
[Bryan] All right, touchdown.

45:22.500 --> 45:23.767
[Thomas] <i>How you feeling,</i>
<i>Bryan?</i>

45:24.867 --> 45:27.367
[Bryan speaking]

45:32.367 --> 45:33.367
[Thomas] <i>Hell, yeah.</i>

45:38.367 --> 45:39.500
[Bryan speaking]

45:41.266 --> 45:42.166
[Thomas] Hose, hose, hose!

45:42.900 --> 45:44.000
[Thomas speaking]

45:46.667 --> 45:48.500
[Thomas] Come up, Bryan,
we lost hose off the jet.

45:49.166 --> 45:50.767
[Bryan speaking]

45:59.166 --> 46:00.567
[Thomas] It came off
the coupler.

46:00.567 --> 46:04.667
[Bryan speaking]

46:04.667 --> 46:07.567
[Thomas] Looks like
our clamp got old
and slipped off.

46:07.567 --> 46:09.867
If we don't have one on board,

46:09.867 --> 46:12.100
we're gonna have to cut
this day short.

46:12.166 --> 46:13.467
Yeah, I wouldn't reuse this.

46:15.000 --> 46:17.100
Yeah, clamps rust out
here in the salt water,

46:17.100 --> 46:18.800
they just get chewed up
real fast.

46:20.767 --> 46:21.467
Oh, look at that.

46:23.066 --> 46:24.266
[producer speaking]

46:24.266 --> 46:26.000
-[Thomas] Yeah.
-I think-- I think so.

46:26.066 --> 46:28.600
[Thomas] We can do it.
We got a clamp, luckily.

46:28.667 --> 46:30.000
[Bryan] Thank God for backups.

46:30.000 --> 46:32.900
One little $2 clamp
could've cost us
ounces of gold today.

46:34.100 --> 46:36.066
Good thing Vernon's not here
to see it. [laughs]

46:36.066 --> 46:37.200
[bleep]

46:37.200 --> 46:39.667
Pretend like
it's your equipment
and not mine.

46:40.467 --> 46:41.367
[Thomas speaking]

46:42.367 --> 46:43.100
[motor whirring]

46:47.166 --> 46:48.900
[Thomas speaking]

46:52.266 --> 46:53.867
[Bryan speaking]

46:58.400 --> 47:00.567
[Bryan speaking]

47:01.200 --> 47:02.367
[Gary] <i>All right.</i>

47:02.367 --> 47:03.800
<i>Well, keep on going, man.</i>

47:03.867 --> 47:05.367
I think Vernon would be proud.

47:05.867 --> 47:07.667
[Bryan] <i>Oh, yeah.</i>

47:07.667 --> 47:12.166
[Bryan speaking]

47:12.567 --> 47:16.567
[speaking]

47:16.567 --> 47:19.000
[Bryan laughs] <i>Oh, yeah, baby.</i>

47:19.066 --> 47:20.467
<i>Whoo!</i>

47:22.867 --> 47:24.266
[narrator] <i>Twelve miles west.</i>

47:34.467 --> 47:36.667
[Zeke speaking]

47:37.767 --> 47:40.467
[Zeke speaking]

47:40.467 --> 47:43.000
[narrator] <i>Zeke Tenhoff</i>
<i>has found gold</i>

47:43.000 --> 47:45.367
<i>between a rock</i>
<i>and a hard place.</i>

47:47.300 --> 47:50.066
[Zeke speaking]

47:51.100 --> 47:53.066
[Zeke speaking]

47:53.800 --> 47:54.467
[Zeke] But...

47:55.467 --> 47:59.000
[Zeke speaking]

48:03.467 --> 48:04.467
Roger that.

48:05.567 --> 48:08.266
[Zeke speaking]

48:11.200 --> 48:12.266
[Zeke] <i>So, if you--</i>

48:12.266 --> 48:13.667
[Zeke continues speaking]

48:14.867 --> 48:16.100
Oh, big time.

48:16.166 --> 48:18.567
[Zeke speaking]

48:20.667 --> 48:22.266
All right, roger that.

48:27.000 --> 48:28.300
Really pumped.

48:28.367 --> 48:31.066
So I'mma get down there,
get the gold,

48:31.066 --> 48:32.867
hopefully get the cheddar.

48:32.867 --> 48:34.300
Get the bread,
you know what I'm saying?

48:34.967 --> 48:37.000
There he is, he's up.

48:37.000 --> 48:38.300
[Zeke] This is really
challenging ground

48:38.367 --> 48:40.600
for Nate's first
Bering Sea dive.

48:40.667 --> 48:42.967
<i>I'm already pretty wiped</i>
<i>from moving all those rocks.</i>

48:42.967 --> 48:45.800
<i>So this'll be good opportunity</i>
<i>to see if he can really</i>

48:45.867 --> 48:47.367
you know,
not just talk the talk,

48:47.367 --> 48:49.467
but like, walk the walk.

48:49.467 --> 48:51.800
I'm [bleep] pumped, baby!
Let's get some gold!

48:53.100 --> 48:55.300
[Zeke] The clock's ticking
on the rest of the summer.

48:55.367 --> 48:57.700
I need Nate to be
a difference-maker.

48:57.767 --> 49:00.867
-[motor whirring]
-Get my little tootsies
warmed up.

49:00.867 --> 49:03.667
See normally,
I just gotta pee in it
to get warm.

49:03.667 --> 49:04.967
[Zeke] Nate's a big guy.

49:04.967 --> 49:07.367
He's like
a crab-fisherman guy.

49:07.367 --> 49:10.000
<i>He's done a bunch</i>
<i>of diving before.</i>

49:10.000 --> 49:13.166
<i>But you never really know</i>
<i>who's gonna like, run with it.</i>

49:26.166 --> 49:28.100
How goes it down there?
You at the bottom?

49:29.000 --> 49:29.967
[Nate speaking]

49:37.066 --> 49:38.500
Yeah, just look around
all over there.

49:38.567 --> 49:40.800
There's a bunch of gold
all through there
that I didn't get yet.

49:43.000 --> 49:45.467
[Zeke speaking]

49:56.100 --> 49:57.867
[Nate speaking]

50:02.000 --> 50:03.367
[Nate continues speaking]

50:04.500 --> 50:05.667
You seeing some gold there?

50:06.467 --> 50:08.266
[Nate speaking]

50:22.266 --> 50:23.567
Yeah, it's extremely obvious.

50:23.567 --> 50:24.667
[Nate continues speaking]

50:33.567 --> 50:35.000
[Nate speaking]

50:42.266 --> 50:45.400
[Kris speaking]

50:51.300 --> 50:53.467
[narrator] <i>On Kris's</i>
<i>first dive of the season,</i>

50:53.467 --> 50:57.100
<i>the captain has swung fortune</i>
<i>toward the Kellys.</i>

50:57.166 --> 51:00.700
[Andy] It feels good
to actually see the gold
that you suck up, huh?

51:00.767 --> 51:04.667
[Kris speaking]

51:04.667 --> 51:07.900
[Andy] <i>Me too.</i>
<i>Like right now,</i>
<i>I have to trust you.</i>

51:07.967 --> 51:09.767
That [bleep]
better be on gold.

51:11.467 --> 51:14.200
[Kris speaking]

51:20.700 --> 51:22.600
It was a rough start
in the beginning.

51:22.667 --> 51:25.367
But we--
we finally relocated
our anchors

51:25.367 --> 51:27.867
and we're on the spot,
we've got a GPS.

51:29.166 --> 51:30.467
Everything's good right now.

51:33.166 --> 51:35.667
<i>He wishes he could bring</i>
<i>his excavator over here</i>

51:35.667 --> 51:38.667
<i>and dig this easy hole</i>
<i>10 feet deep.</i>

51:38.667 --> 51:40.967
<i>We're making money now</i>
<i>with this load.</i>

51:40.967 --> 51:43.800
But the <i>Mistress</i> seems to be
a non-profit organization.

51:43.867 --> 51:44.600
[laughs] You know
what I mean?

51:44.667 --> 51:46.000
You just put money into it.

51:46.000 --> 51:47.367
They don't get money
out of it.

51:47.367 --> 51:49.367
[laughs]

51:51.867 --> 51:54.100
[Brad] <i>Okay, Kris, you've been</i>
<i>down for four hours now.</i>

51:54.100 --> 51:55.367
<i>You ready to come up?</i>

51:55.367 --> 51:57.567
Yes, I think I'm ready
to come up.

51:58.667 --> 52:00.367
[Kris speaking]

52:00.367 --> 52:02.266
Okay, I'll have him
get suited up right now.

52:03.000 --> 52:04.100
Here he comes.

52:07.166 --> 52:08.000
So I did it.

52:08.000 --> 52:09.600
I finally accomplished
our mission.

52:09.667 --> 52:12.600
As leader
of the Reaper Nation,
I got us on gold.

52:12.667 --> 52:14.066
Now the next step.

52:14.066 --> 52:15.500
What is up?
Let's go get some gold.

52:16.767 --> 52:18.900
Train Anthony
so we can get
a solid dive team

52:18.967 --> 52:20.867
going on the <i>Reaper</i>
at all times.

52:20.867 --> 52:21.834
We need this

52:21.867 --> 52:23.400
if we have any chance
of hitting our goal

52:23.467 --> 52:24.767
before the summer ends.

52:24.767 --> 52:27.867
I didn't really explain
the trudging at all
to Anthony.

52:27.867 --> 52:30.300
So we're just gonna throw
Anthony underneath the water,

52:30.367 --> 52:32.367
give him a little
trial by fire.

52:32.367 --> 52:33.266
But I'm gonna tell you,

52:33.266 --> 52:34.967
I know
he's gonna make it work.

52:34.967 --> 52:38.100
Because the nozzle is sitting
six inches from gold.

52:38.166 --> 52:40.100
All he has to do
is move the [bleep]
thing around

52:40.166 --> 52:41.767
and he's gonna get gold.

52:43.000 --> 52:44.867
[Kris] <i>Anthony is</i>
<i>an underwater welder.</i>

52:44.867 --> 52:46.867
That's a pretty serious gig.

52:46.867 --> 52:48.900
It's a lot simpler
than it looks.

52:49.500 --> 52:50.500
It really is.

52:50.567 --> 52:52.166
I have a lot of faith in you.

52:52.166 --> 52:54.367
-Gotcha.
-I really do.

52:54.367 --> 52:56.367
But he's never dredged
for gold anywhere,

52:56.367 --> 52:57.567
let alone the Bering Sea.

52:59.800 --> 53:01.667
Hopefully,
it doesn't overwhelm him.

53:01.667 --> 53:03.200
[motor whirring]

53:03.266 --> 53:04.900
[Kris] You're good.
Yeah, you're good.

53:04.967 --> 53:05.900
Go.

53:10.266 --> 53:13.266
Sometimes, you know,
you need that push.

53:13.266 --> 53:15.367
You know?
'Cause you're thinking
about it too much.

53:15.367 --> 53:17.967
I knew he was thinking
about it too much.

53:24.166 --> 53:26.266
[Anthony speaking]

53:26.266 --> 53:28.066
[Kris] <i>Okay, now,</i>
<i>there's two ways</i>
<i>you can do this.</i>

53:28.066 --> 53:30.066
<i>You can either</i>
<i>be on your knees</i>
<i>and suck it up</i>

53:30.066 --> 53:32.266
<i>or you can stand up there</i>
<i>like a vacuum cleaner.</i>

53:34.066 --> 53:34.867
[Anthony speaking]

53:39.100 --> 53:40.367
He's just getting
his feel for it.

53:40.367 --> 53:41.767
But it's like,
right off the bat,

53:41.767 --> 53:43.500
he goes down there,
he takes the hose off,

53:43.567 --> 53:44.500
he goes right to work.

53:48.000 --> 53:49.166
[Kris] <i>Do you see</i>
<i>any gold yet?</i>

53:51.100 --> 53:52.066
[Anthony speaking]

53:53.767 --> 53:54.800
[Kris speaking]

53:59.266 --> 53:59.900
[Anthony speaking]

54:01.767 --> 54:03.667
[Kris speaking]

54:03.667 --> 54:04.433
[Anthony speaking]

54:06.000 --> 54:07.567
And when you see
black [bleep]

54:07.567 --> 54:09.667
that's where the gold hides.

54:09.667 --> 54:11.867
So make sure you vacuum that
a little harder.

54:11.867 --> 54:13.066
[Anthony] <i>Roger.</i>

54:13.066 --> 54:14.100
Okay. There you go.

54:17.700 --> 54:19.100
He's not much of a talker.

54:19.166 --> 54:21.166
To be honest with you,
he's got that Southern drawl.

54:21.166 --> 54:24.066
I can only understand
what the [bleep]
he says half the time anyway,

54:24.066 --> 54:25.000
so we're cool.

54:34.967 --> 54:35.900
What's the matter?

54:41.266 --> 54:43.667
[man speaking]

54:45.166 --> 54:46.867
[Kris] Okay,
stop for a second.

54:46.867 --> 54:49.166
And uh,
clip the nozzle on its side.

54:51.300 --> 54:52.233
[Anthony] Okay.

54:53.700 --> 54:55.800
Stick your hand
kind of in front of it.

54:55.867 --> 54:58.000
Do you feel a lot
of suction going on?

55:01.300 --> 55:02.266
[Anthony] Uh...

55:02.767 --> 55:03.667
[Anthony speaking]

55:04.367 --> 55:06.100
[Kris speaking]

55:07.367 --> 55:08.166
[Anthony speaking]

55:08.166 --> 55:09.300
[bleep] Man.

55:10.767 --> 55:12.667
It's not going good
our first time.

55:14.600 --> 55:15.900
[Kris] <i>Here's the thing</i>
<i>about dredging.</i>

55:15.967 --> 55:17.967
<i>In theory,</i>
<i>it sounds easy.</i>

55:17.967 --> 55:20.767
<i>Big giant vacuum cleaner</i>
<i>suck up free money.</i>

55:20.767 --> 55:22.166
But it's way harder
than it looks.

55:22.166 --> 55:23.800
And I should've gave him
more of a tutorial

55:23.867 --> 55:26.400
before just throwing him
down there.

55:26.467 --> 55:29.200
<i>Now he's stuck on a rock jam</i>
<i>and it sound like a nasty one.</i>

55:32.667 --> 55:34.700
Okay, man,
just hook it up
and we're done.

55:34.767 --> 55:36.266
I'm gonna take you
back to the harbor

55:36.266 --> 55:38.867
and I'll give you
a full demonstration
on what we're doing.

55:39.667 --> 55:41.567
[Anthony speaking]

55:41.567 --> 55:43.266
I'm not pissed,
don't worry about it.

55:43.266 --> 55:44.500
You did a good job.

55:46.400 --> 55:47.800
[Anthony speaking]

55:53.767 --> 55:54.734
So we're gonna pack up.

55:54.734 --> 55:57.000
But we'll clean the rock jam
out on shore.

55:58.600 --> 55:59.467
[Anthony speaking]

55:59.467 --> 56:01.200
[Kris speaking]

56:01.266 --> 56:03.166
-[Anthony speaking]
-[Kris speaking]

56:03.166 --> 56:04.600
[Kris speaking]

56:10.467 --> 56:11.667
[Kris continues speaking]

56:14.667 --> 56:16.500
[Kris speaking]

56:16.567 --> 56:17.367
[Anthony speaking]

56:22.767 --> 56:24.700
I should've stayed
down there myself.

56:31.367 --> 56:32.667
[Kris] Could be better.
[clears throat]

56:33.967 --> 56:36.266
It couldn't have gone
any worse with Anthony.

56:36.266 --> 56:37.667
Oh, yeah, I guess
it could've.

56:37.667 --> 56:39.166
He could've freaked out.

56:39.166 --> 56:41.567
He could've tried [bleep]
drowning himself.

56:41.567 --> 56:43.000
Did you hear his breathing
when he hit that water?

56:43.000 --> 56:44.400
[breathing heavily]

56:44.467 --> 56:46.667
-You're spitting all over me.
-I know I was.

56:46.667 --> 56:48.500
Imagine him
spitting in my mask.

56:48.567 --> 56:50.266
You'll be fine.

56:51.200 --> 56:54.000
[Kris] <i>As the captain,</i>
<i>I need people to have</i>
<i>belief in themselves.</i>

56:54.066 --> 56:55.567
<i>Belief in the dream.</i>

56:55.567 --> 56:58.767
<i>It's up to me to keep</i>
<i>Anthony's faith in himself</i>
<i>strong.</i>

56:58.767 --> 57:00.900
Otherwise,
he'll never succeed and--

57:00.967 --> 57:02.467
We won't have
the crew we need.

57:02.467 --> 57:04.900
I really want him
to become a vital team player

57:04.967 --> 57:05.934
for <i>Reaper</i> mining.

57:08.000 --> 57:10.300
[Kris] Don't worry, my friend.
I love you.

57:10.367 --> 57:12.300
And it's gonna take
a hell of a lot of problems

57:12.367 --> 57:14.100
for me to stop loving you.

57:14.100 --> 57:15.800
You never have to worry
about that.

57:15.867 --> 57:17.100
Hey, let me tell you what.

57:17.166 --> 57:18.600
[Anthony speaking]

57:18.667 --> 57:21.367
You made it into my place
in my life

57:21.367 --> 57:22.767
that is really hard
to get out of.

57:22.767 --> 57:25.767
I now consider you
one of my good friends.

57:25.767 --> 57:27.266
-[Anthony speaking]
-You don't--

57:27.266 --> 57:30.300
I know, but you know,
like, let me tell you
why you're gonna be okay.

57:30.367 --> 57:31.867
I take care
of my good friends.

57:33.200 --> 57:35.600
<i>And we still have</i>
<i>enough of the season</i>

57:35.667 --> 57:37.967
<i>that we can turn this around</i>
<i>and make some money.</i>

57:50.200 --> 57:51.600
[Emily] Hey, Jeffrey.

57:51.667 --> 57:53.367
How's the ground
looking, dude?

57:55.200 --> 57:56.100
[Jeff speaking]

57:56.867 --> 57:58.767
I mean,
this should be every bit of--

57:58.767 --> 58:00.867
you know,
at least an ounce an hour,
ounce and a half.

58:03.000 --> 58:04.066
[Emily] [bleep]
<i>That's awesome, dude.</i>

58:04.400 --> 58:05.600
[Jeff] Yeah.

58:06.166 --> 58:07.100
[Jane] Wow.

58:07.867 --> 58:09.667
Definitely a good day
for gold.

58:09.667 --> 58:13.567
[Jeff speaking]

58:13.567 --> 58:14.867
<i>I think this is</i>
<i>really gonna pay off.</i>

58:15.367 --> 58:16.867
[Emily] Yay!

58:16.867 --> 58:18.367
Nice.

58:18.367 --> 58:20.066
[narrator] <i>To finish out</i>
<i>the home stretch</i>
<i>of the season,</i>

58:20.066 --> 58:23.600
<i>Emily's brought</i>
<i>in heavy hitter,</i>
<i>Jeff Orzechowski.</i>

58:23.667 --> 58:24.867
[Jeff] I'm seeing color

58:26.166 --> 58:28.700
every time I move
one of these rocks
on the bottom.

58:28.767 --> 58:30.000
[Emily] <i>Oh,</i>
<i>that sounds awesome.</i>

58:30.467 --> 58:31.734
Whoo!

58:31.734 --> 58:34.200
[narrator] <i>And the crew</i>
<i>is firing on all cylinders.</i>

58:34.266 --> 58:35.367
[Emily] Good to have a team

58:35.367 --> 58:37.767
that knows how to find
and follow and produce gold.

58:37.767 --> 58:39.367
[Jeff] Oh, there we go.
Perfect.

58:40.767 --> 58:43.967
I mean, I can see some gold
right on top of this stuff.

58:51.467 --> 58:53.467
[Emily] It's getting
a bit choppy.

58:53.467 --> 58:54.166
Copy?

58:55.200 --> 58:57.467
[Jeff speaking]

58:57.467 --> 58:58.166
[Emily] Roger.

58:58.767 --> 59:01.266
[groaning]

59:02.367 --> 59:03.967
[Jeff speaking]

59:10.667 --> 59:12.266
[Emily] Yeah, dude,
this sucks.

59:13.767 --> 59:16.166
[Emily] <i>We're at the point</i>
<i>in the season</i>
<i>where it's make or break.</i>

59:16.166 --> 59:17.867
But you don't wanna push it
too hard.

59:17.867 --> 59:20.166
There's still a line
that you can't cross.

59:20.166 --> 59:21.600
[Emily speaking]

59:23.467 --> 59:24.867
[Jeff] Ah, [bleep].

59:28.867 --> 59:30.800
[Emily] <i>We still have</i>
<i>a couple more days</i>
<i>to mine but,</i>

59:30.867 --> 59:33.567
we can't damage the rig
or get people hurt.

59:35.266 --> 59:35.934
[Emily] Oh!

59:37.100 --> 59:38.166
We gotta get out
of here.

59:38.166 --> 59:39.867
This weather's
not goofing around.

59:39.867 --> 59:40.767
The weather's changed,

59:40.767 --> 59:42.767
the diver's been down
long enough but,

59:42.767 --> 59:44.200
we're gonna put
a marker buoy down,

59:44.266 --> 59:46.400
so when we come back,
we're gonna start
right back here.

59:46.467 --> 59:48.500
They were like,
"It's called a marker buoy."

59:48.567 --> 59:50.100
So basically,
the diver just comes up

59:50.100 --> 59:53.266
and grabs the anchor
and takes it down to his spot.

59:53.266 --> 59:55.567
And the buoy lets us know
up top where it's at.

59:56.000 --> 59:56.767
Hey, Jane.

59:57.600 --> 59:59.266
