<i>out here.</i>

1:11:57.100 --> 1:12:00.066
There's no rest
for the wicked when the end
of the season's near.

1:12:01.300 --> 1:12:03.400
The night crew is here
right now.

1:12:03.467 --> 1:12:06.800
Yeah, hopefully
the night shift goes as smooth
as day shift,

1:12:06.867 --> 1:12:11.800
and we can, uh, be happy,
and pay all the bills,

1:12:11.867 --> 1:12:13.767
and maybe get some
of my money back.

1:12:14.500 --> 1:12:15.867
Steady as she goes.

1:12:22.100 --> 1:12:24.266
Well, you can see it in there.

1:12:24.266 --> 1:12:27.800
Yup, we just might put some
gold in the box.

1:12:27.867 --> 1:12:30.667
Night sift here,
getting everything greased.

1:12:30.667 --> 1:12:33.266
Checking oil. Box looks good.

1:12:33.266 --> 1:12:35.200
All right,
let's get out of here.

1:12:35.900 --> 1:12:37.166
Brr!

1:12:37.967 --> 1:12:42.166
Successful trip.
Feels good to put
some gold in the box.

1:12:46.667 --> 1:12:48.166
[narrator] <i>12 miles east...</i>

1:12:51.767 --> 1:12:54.166
[Thomas] All right, Bryan.
You've been down there
four hours.

1:12:54.166 --> 1:12:55.300
You ready to come up?

1:12:56.400 --> 1:12:58.266
[Bryan speaking on radio]

1:13:01.700 --> 1:13:02.867
[Thomas] Copy.

1:13:02.900 --> 1:13:06.200
All right,
I'm gonna start pulling
your umbilical up.

1:13:06.266 --> 1:13:10.100
[narrator] <i>With two</i>
<i>dive shifts, and eight hours</i>
<i>banked on the box...</i>

1:13:11.667 --> 1:13:14.100
[Bryan speaking]

1:13:14.100 --> 1:13:16.500
[narrator] <i>...the</i> Wild Ranger
<i>crew's flourished</i>

1:13:16.567 --> 1:13:19.700
<i>despite the absence</i>
<i>of their cantankerous leader.</i>

1:13:24.066 --> 1:13:26.100
-You ready?
-[Bryan] Wait. Go.

1:13:31.767 --> 1:13:33.667
[Thomas] Do you want me
to start pulling the rear?

1:13:33.667 --> 1:13:36.166
All right, all buoys are up.

1:13:36.166 --> 1:13:40.266
<i>Yeah, uh, we put some gold</i>
<i>in the box,</i>
<i>we got some time on.</i>

1:13:40.266 --> 1:13:43.867
I'm working the systems
like I would with Vernon here,

1:13:43.867 --> 1:13:45.700
but he's not here, so...

1:13:45.767 --> 1:13:47.400
<i>It's running smooth.</i>

1:13:47.467 --> 1:13:49.600
<i>Our divers got in,</i>
<i>our divers got out.</i>

1:13:49.667 --> 1:13:52.767
We got off the claim,
we're heading back
to shore, so...

1:13:52.767 --> 1:13:54.600
<i>Today was a successful day</i>
<i>in my book.</i>

1:13:55.100 --> 1:13:56.367
[Cary speaking]

1:14:00.767 --> 1:14:02.567
[Thomas] Let's go home,
get some sleep.

1:14:02.567 --> 1:14:04.567
Hey, today was
a good day, guys. Good job!

1:14:15.500 --> 1:14:19.867
I think the idea
of using divining rods
is really interesting.

1:14:19.867 --> 1:14:22.166
It's an ancient method
to find gold.

1:14:23.300 --> 1:14:26.266
<i>Anything that science</i>
<i>can't explain</i>

1:14:26.266 --> 1:14:27.667
we've really
just called magic,

1:14:27.667 --> 1:14:31.000
but there's
a lot of things in the world
that we consider magic

1:14:31.000 --> 1:14:33.567
that really are just things
we haven't been able
to explain.

1:14:35.667 --> 1:14:42.066
Magic is... it's something
that's operating regardless
of one's belief.

1:14:42.066 --> 1:14:45.600
So, in some, maybe,
quantum idea,

1:14:45.667 --> 1:14:49.000
uh, it's very possible
that there's some kind of

1:14:49.066 --> 1:14:54.867
intrinsic connection
between us and, uh,
the surrounding natural world.

1:14:54.867 --> 1:14:57.867
<i>It's kind of like</i>
<i>the placebo effect,</i>
<i>you know, uh.</i>

1:14:57.867 --> 1:15:02.667
<i>Does the placebo effect...</i>
<i>how exactly does it work?</i>

1:15:02.667 --> 1:15:04.867
In some kind of way,
there's the law of attraction.

1:15:04.867 --> 1:15:08.166
So, I think that, uh,
a big principle

1:15:08.166 --> 1:15:11.467
in the idea of, uh, you know,
dousing for gold,

1:15:11.467 --> 1:15:14.767
is, uh, this idea
that the law of attraction

1:15:14.767 --> 1:15:18.000
is this, sort of,
quantum field

1:15:18.066 --> 1:15:20.100
that we don't
fully understand.

1:15:20.100 --> 1:15:24.100
<i>Even the top</i>
<i>quantum physicists</i>
<i>still don't fully understand</i>

1:15:24.166 --> 1:15:26.800
<i>some of the nuances</i>
<i>of how the universe works.</i>

1:15:26.867 --> 1:15:29.734
So, it's cool to think
about the possibilities

1:15:29.734 --> 1:15:33.567
and the law of attraction
with gold is strong as
it ever was, you know.

1:15:49.667 --> 1:15:51.066
[Bryan] All right, all right.

1:15:52.266 --> 1:15:53.600
That's what I'm talking about.

1:15:55.734 --> 1:15:57.300
There, there, there it is.

1:15:58.667 --> 1:15:59.967
Oh, there's lots of gold
there already.

1:16:00.800 --> 1:16:04.400
I'm glad Bryan likes
to clean gold.

1:16:04.467 --> 1:16:07.066
[chuckles] <i>Because it's not</i>
<i>my favorite thing to do.</i>

1:16:07.066 --> 1:16:10.400
Stayed bent over
for that long,
I can't get unbent.

1:16:10.467 --> 1:16:12.066
[narrator] <i>The skipper's</i>
<i>back in town...</i>

1:16:12.066 --> 1:16:13.567
[Bryan] That sight
never gets old.

1:16:14.867 --> 1:16:17.600
-You done?
-All right, let's see
what we got.

1:16:17.667 --> 1:16:19.400
[narrator] <i>...and it's time</i>
<i>for the crew</i>

1:16:19.467 --> 1:16:22.000
<i>to show the boss</i>
<i>what they're made of.</i>

1:16:22.066 --> 1:16:24.266
I'm, uh... I'm, uh,
somewhat impressed.

1:16:24.266 --> 1:16:26.967
-[Bryan] Not bad, huh?
-I mean, you guys weren't
pulling your pud

1:16:26.967 --> 1:16:28.467
-for all that time.
-[chuckles] No, we actually--

1:16:28.467 --> 1:16:31.300
I mean, there's really...
I don't even wanna hear

1:16:31.367 --> 1:16:33.567
-about what happened
while I was gone.
-You don't wanna know.

1:16:33.567 --> 1:16:34.967
-You don't wanna know.
-Okay?

1:16:34.967 --> 1:16:38.166
-We made a pact
not to say anything.
-The boat is still afloat.

1:16:38.166 --> 1:16:41.200
All right, some things
I'd just rather not
know about.

1:16:41.266 --> 1:16:44.367
-Close the door
and we'll talk about it later.
-[all chuckling]

1:16:44.367 --> 1:16:47.300
[Vernon] <i>When the cat's away</i>
<i>the mice will play.</i>

1:16:47.367 --> 1:16:50.734
And it's possible
that what went on
on my absence,

1:16:50.734 --> 1:16:52.500
could make me hit the roof.

1:16:52.567 --> 1:16:54.767
<i>But as long as there's gold</i>
<i>in the box,</i>

1:16:54.767 --> 1:16:56.767
and the equipment
is still afloat,

1:16:56.767 --> 1:16:58.100
it's all good, baby.

1:16:58.100 --> 1:16:59.266
-[Bryan] Ready?
-[Vernon] Yeah.

1:16:59.266 --> 1:17:00.467
[Bryan] Here we go.

1:17:04.100 --> 1:17:08.467
One, two, three, four,
oh we hit five.

1:17:08.467 --> 1:17:10.767
-5.3.
-[Cary] 5.3.

1:17:10.767 --> 1:17:12.867
-[Bryan] Nice.
-[Cary] Yeah,
not too bad, huh?

1:17:12.867 --> 1:17:16.000
-[Bryan] Geez, you come home
to five ounces.
-[Cary] Yeah, there you go.

1:17:16.066 --> 1:17:19.166
[narrator] <i>5.3 ounces is worth</i>
<i>over nine grand.</i>

1:17:19.166 --> 1:17:21.667
<i>And while it's not exactly</i>
<i>breaking the bank,</i>

1:17:21.667 --> 1:17:26.000
<i>it was a profitable day</i>
<i>for the leaderless gold ship.</i>

1:17:26.000 --> 1:17:29.467
Well, I mean, it keeps us
in the game, that's all
I gotta say.

1:17:29.467 --> 1:17:31.367
I mean, you made something
while I was gone.

1:17:31.367 --> 1:17:33.800
Believe me, that's...
that is a load
off my shoulders.

1:17:33.867 --> 1:17:36.000
I mean, I gotta be able
to trust somebody

1:17:36.000 --> 1:17:37.367
with the boat
when I'm not here,

1:17:37.367 --> 1:17:39.800
'cause I'm not
gonna be here all the time.

1:17:39.867 --> 1:17:41.567
<i>I gotta give it to the guys.</i>

1:17:41.567 --> 1:17:42.900
<i>They kept us in the game,</i>

1:17:42.967 --> 1:17:44.667
and it looks like
they might have landed us

1:17:44.667 --> 1:17:46.567
on a decent pay streak too.

1:17:46.567 --> 1:17:49.166
Maybe this is just
the spark we're looking for

1:17:49.166 --> 1:17:51.767
to ride the rest
of the season,

1:17:51.767 --> 1:17:54.500
<i>and who knows</i>
<i>there may still be</i>
<i>sandy beaches,</i>

1:17:54.567 --> 1:17:56.500
<i>and hula dancers in my future.</i>

1:17:56.567 --> 1:18:00.066
Bottom line is,
she's still afloat,
nobody got hurt,

1:18:00.066 --> 1:18:02.200
-we got gold in the box.
-That's all that counts.

1:18:02.266 --> 1:18:03.767
-Great job.
-All right.

1:18:03.767 --> 1:18:05.266
Boom 'em, Danno.

1:18:05.266 --> 1:18:06.367
Bag it and tag it.

1:18:09.500 --> 1:18:11.000
[narrator] <i>On the other side</i>
<i>of town...</i>

1:18:23.767 --> 1:18:26.200
Please let there be
a lot of gold.

1:18:26.266 --> 1:18:28.266
[narrator] <i>After a day</i>
<i>of highs and lows</i>

1:18:28.266 --> 1:18:31.100
<i>the Kellys are hoping</i>
<i>for a little Irish luck.</i>

1:18:33.200 --> 1:18:34.767
That's not looking
that promising.

1:18:35.867 --> 1:18:37.367
I hope it's not
the worst cleanup

1:18:37.367 --> 1:18:40.100
that I've had
in a really long time,

1:18:40.100 --> 1:18:43.266
'cause, literally,
I know I saw
more gold than that.

1:18:43.266 --> 1:18:45.300
There should be,
like, wow gold.

1:18:45.367 --> 1:18:47.266
There's definitely not
wow gold.

1:18:47.266 --> 1:18:49.300
It's like, "Wow.
Where is the gold?"

1:18:51.166 --> 1:18:53.467
At this point in the season,
I'm looking for a miracle.

1:18:54.467 --> 1:18:56.567
<i>A miracle</i>
<i>that the</i> Mistress <i>returns,</i>

1:18:56.567 --> 1:18:58.767
<i>a miracle that</i>
<i>the dive team's clicking,</i>

1:18:58.767 --> 1:19:02.367
<i>and a miracle</i>
<i>that we get enough gold</i>
<i>to keep Reaper Nation alive.</i>

1:19:02.367 --> 1:19:04.266
The truth is
that's a lot of miracles,

1:19:04.266 --> 1:19:05.800
and there's
not enough time left,

1:19:05.867 --> 1:19:07.900
but it's all I've got
to keep me going right now.

1:19:08.867 --> 1:19:11.367
Hey, you know what?
It's our first clean up.

1:19:11.367 --> 1:19:13.900
We've had a lot
of problems getting this gold,

1:19:13.967 --> 1:19:16.600
you know, so,
at least this right here,

1:19:16.667 --> 1:19:18.667
will give everyone
a little money
in their pocket.

1:19:21.867 --> 1:19:23.100
Okay, here we go.

1:19:23.100 --> 1:19:26.400
We are definitely
not millionaires.

1:19:27.567 --> 1:19:29.100
We're not even thousandaires.

1:19:33.867 --> 1:19:37.667
-[Anthony] Almost two ounces.
-1.86.

1:19:37.667 --> 1:19:41.867
[narrator] <i>1.86 ounces</i>
<i>is worth 3,300 bucks.</i>

1:19:41.867 --> 1:19:47.200
<i>Nowhere near</i>
<i>what they need to make</i>
<i>their $125,000 payment.</i>

1:19:47.266 --> 1:19:49.767
[Kris] Worst gold cleanup
we've had in so long,

1:19:49.767 --> 1:19:51.000
but everything's working
at least.

1:19:51.066 --> 1:19:52.500
Okay, let's call it a day.

1:19:52.500 --> 1:19:55.467
Get ready out there,
and get ready for the next
nice day of mining.

1:19:58.066 --> 1:20:00.166
Well, so much for miracles.

1:20:00.166 --> 1:20:02.100
So I'm trying to keep
a positive attitude

1:20:02.100 --> 1:20:05.467
to the team, but basically
I'm lying to myself.

1:20:05.467 --> 1:20:07.266
It's a [bleep] joke.

1:20:07.266 --> 1:20:09.266
I was on amazing gold.

1:20:10.767 --> 1:20:12.400
I don't wanna give up
on Reaper Nation,

1:20:12.467 --> 1:20:13.900
but it's not
looking good right now.

1:20:13.967 --> 1:20:16.166
I'm just hoping right now,
in these final days,

1:20:16.166 --> 1:20:18.900
we can turn everything
right around.

1:20:18.967 --> 1:20:22.266
By, hopefully next week,
we'll be running
the <i>Mistress</i> again.

1:20:22.266 --> 1:20:25.867
But hopefully,
we start getting
some real time in.

1:20:25.867 --> 1:20:28.567
Hopefully, start killing it
24 hours a day.

1:20:29.567 --> 1:20:31.100
I know that's
a lot of hopefully.

1:20:35.467 --> 1:20:36.567
[narrator] <i>Across town...</i>

1:20:45.367 --> 1:20:47.567
[Shawn] <i>Had a good day</i>
<i>of mining.</i>

1:20:47.567 --> 1:20:50.200
<i>Everything was working.</i>

1:20:50.266 --> 1:20:52.166
<i>Dave was in town,</i>
<i>we had some good weather,</i>

1:20:52.166 --> 1:20:53.800
<i>got out there and mined.</i>

1:20:53.867 --> 1:20:56.967
Let's see if we made it count.

1:20:56.967 --> 1:21:00.100
[narrator] <i>After a round</i>
<i>in the ring with</i>
<i>the newly repaired</i> Myrtle,

1:21:00.100 --> 1:21:03.100
<i>Shawn's ready to reap</i>
<i>the rewards.</i>

1:21:03.166 --> 1:21:04.467
[Shawn] <i>We were</i>
<i>on the good stuff.</i>

1:21:04.467 --> 1:21:06.166
We kept her going
through the night

1:21:06.166 --> 1:21:08.000
I'm expecting
to see triple digits.

1:21:12.567 --> 1:21:14.867
I need 3,000 ounces
this summer.

1:21:14.867 --> 1:21:17.166
So, I'm hoping to go big
the rest of the season.

1:21:18.767 --> 1:21:20.266
Let's see what we got.

1:21:20.266 --> 1:21:21.300
Here we go.

1:21:21.734 --> 1:21:22.567
Bam!

1:21:24.567 --> 1:21:27.734
There's 20, 30, 40...

1:21:28.500 --> 1:21:30.200
50, 90, 100.

1:21:31.166 --> 1:21:34.767
18, 120.

1:21:36.734 --> 1:21:38.066
We have a pile of gold.

1:21:39.166 --> 1:21:43.900
[narrator] <i>120 ounces</i>
<i>is worth over $215,000,</i>

1:21:43.967 --> 1:21:47.967
<i>and the</i> Myrtle
<i>and her captain are primed</i>
<i>for a big finish this summer.</i>

1:21:49.166 --> 1:21:51.467
[Shawn] Really good
<i>Myrtle</i> cleanup.

1:21:51.467 --> 1:21:53.867
Put this away,
get it in the jar.

1:21:53.867 --> 1:21:57.166
Best sound ever
is gold piling up.

1:21:57.166 --> 1:21:59.066
<i>When the</i> Myrtle's <i>firing</i>
<i>on all cylinders</i>

1:21:59.066 --> 1:22:00.967
<i>there's nothing like her</i>
<i>on the Bering Sea.</i>

1:22:02.100 --> 1:22:04.300
If she doesn't give me
any more fits

1:22:04.367 --> 1:22:07.734
the sky is the limit,
and 3,000 ounces
is within reach.

1:22:09.100 --> 1:22:12.166
<i>All the operations</i>
<i>are hitting on</i>
<i>all the cylinders.</i>

1:22:12.166 --> 1:22:13.433
<i>Here we go.</i>

1:22:15.500 --> 1:22:18.734
[narrator] <i>The pendulum swings</i>
<i>in Shawn's direction</i>

1:22:18.734 --> 1:22:21.600
<i>while Emily and Zeke</i>
<i>hold strong,</i>

1:22:21.667 --> 1:22:25.567
<i>and Kris, well,</i>
<i>he's going to need</i>
<i>those miracles.</i>

1:22:26.800 --> 1:22:29.500
<i>Next time, on</i> Bering Sea Gold.

1:22:29.567 --> 1:22:31.300
This is gonna be a good one.

1:22:31.367 --> 1:22:33.367
[laughs] Oh, yeah.

1:22:33.367 --> 1:22:36.000
Man, I love it when
a plan comes together.

1:22:36.066 --> 1:22:39.100
<i>Dig until the weather turns.</i>

1:22:39.166 --> 1:22:41.200
[man on radio] <i>Don't know</i>
<i>what the weather's doing,</i>
<i>just keep an eye on it.</i>

1:22:41.266 --> 1:22:43.200
[Nate speaking on radio]

1:22:43.266 --> 1:22:45.500
[Zeke] I want you to hook
the nozzle up and come up.

1:22:45.567 --> 1:22:46.467
[Nate grunts]

1:22:48.800 --> 1:22:50.000
<i>They're dead in the water,</i>

1:22:50.000 --> 1:22:51.900
<i>a coast guard</i>
<i>is nowhere around.</i> [bleep]

1:22:53.867 --> 1:22:56.066
[Shawn] We're gonna go
find him, get him home safe.

1:22:56.066 --> 1:22:58.166
-[thuds]
-[bleep]

1:22:58.600 --> 1:23:00.300
It is rough.

1:23:00.367 --> 1:23:02.166
Hey, you guys.
He's right there. I got him.

1:23:02.166 --> 1:23:06.667
[shouts] Abandon ship,
my engines are swamping.

1:23:06.667 --> 1:23:08.767
-We got some damage
to the boat.
-[producer] Guys! Hey.

1:23:11.467 --> 1:23:12.667
[Thomas] Let's go [bleep].

1:23:12.734 --> 1:23:14.567
There's a hole right here
going through the boat.

1:23:14.567 --> 1:23:17.867
I gotta get out of here.
Watch out, guys,
this is a big one.

1:23:18.166 --> 1:23:19.300
Hang on!
